
[1]orthodox

   OR'THODOX, a. [See Orthodoxy.]

   1. Sound in the christian faith; believing the genuine doctrines taught
   in the Scriptures; opposed to heretical; as an orthodox christian.

   2. According with the doctrines of Scripture; as an orthodox creed or
   faith.
